column5: Was out this morning on Cooks, got into a nice 37.5 inch healthy pike, great fight, released unharmed. One reason it sucks fishing alone is its hard to get a decent picture...
Sweet gator! I just got back from my pike trip up north, i might have to get out for some simcoe gators after some carpin.
Vertical hold, tsk, tsk     I agree. Hold the traditional way by the eye balls is better.LOL
Post any more photos like that you'll have a list of potential fishing buddies!  Nice gator

One reason it sucks fishing alone is its hard to get a decent picture...  Very nice pike indeed.  Pretty simple to make a basic camera holder  for when your alone in the boat.  Piece of wooden dowel that's fit your rear seat post hole with a 3 sided box fasted to the top to hold your camera.  Set the auto timer, lift the fish & smile
you should practice on your selfies
Pike selfie?, lew, not a bad idea.  I only held it that way so I could get an ok picture, would be hard to hold the pike with two hands horizontally and take the picture too, lol.
Nice Pike anywhere, Congrats Tight Lines SBK
